Just what are the likely political shockwaves of the revival or burial of the recently nullified building bridges initiative reforms? Well, this is the question in the minds of top political guns, their strategists and analysts alike, as the court of appeal sits to decide the fate of the BBI bill, in an appeal that involves among other parties president Uhuru Kenyatta and former prime minister Raila Odinga. tonight, on our continuing special series ahead of this landmark ruling, our senior political affairs reporter Murimi Mwangi, paints the picture of likely options for top political leaders as the Friday BBI date with the court draws closer.